===Etymology===
;"northern foreigners"
:{{unknown|zh}}. {{zh-ref|Goldin (2011)}} proposes that {{zh-l|狄}}/{{zh-l|翟}} was a "pseudo-ethnonym" and meant "feathered"; {{w|Liji}} mentioned that the Dí's clothings were made of birds' feathers and mammals' hairs[https://ctext.org/liji/wang-zhi?searchu=%E7%8B%84&searchmode=showall#result]. If so, see {{zh-l|翟}} for more etymology.

;"low servant"
:Either based on the northern foreigners' endo-ethnonym, or more likely {{der|zh|aav}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). Compare {{w|Monic languages|Proto-Monic}} *'''ɗiik''', {{w|Bahnaric languages|Proto-Bahnaric}} *'''ɗɨc''', as well as {{cog|mkh-pro|**ɗiək ~ ɗiik ~ *ɗik||slave}}.

